cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper focuses on supervised aspect extraction using a modified CNN, which is a common technique in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of control modules to prevent over-fitting and boost performance, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses deep learning techniques, which are often associated with artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The aspect extraction task also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE).
